OL,5, Six years ago, a Muslim boy returned   
OL,6, red-faced from a well-known school in  
OL,7, the northern Indian city of Agra.      
OL,9,F"My classmates called me a Pakistani   
OL,10,Fterrorist," the nine-year-old told his 
OL,11,Fmother.                                
OL,13,FReema Ahmad, an author and counsellor, 
OL,14,Fremembers the day vividly.             
OL,16,F"Here was a feisty, little boy with his
OL,17,Ffists clenched so tightly that there   
OL,18,Fwere nail marks in his palm. He was so 
OL,19,Fangry."                                
